claim.claim-text:
3. A control apparatus comprising: 
a variable valve apparatus for changing a valve variable quantity of an intake valve and/or exhaust valve of an engine; 
an oil-pressure control valve for adjusting an oil pressure for driving the variable valve apparatus; and 
a control means for outputting a control signal for controlling the oil-pressure control valve; 
wherein the oil-pressure control valve has a nonlinear control characteristic including a dead band, which exhibits a slow response or all but no response to a change in the control signal, as a portion of a control area, and 
the control means has a vibration means for vibrating the control signal at a predetermined amplitude.

22. A control apparatus comprising: 
a variable valve apparatus for changing a variable quantity of an intake valve and/or exhaust valve of an engien; 
an oil-pressure control valve for adjusting an oil pressure for driving the variable valve apparatus, and 
the oil-pressure control valve has a non-linear control characteristic including a dead band, which exhibits a slow response or all but no response to a change in the control signal, as a portion of a control area; 
a control means for outputting a control signal for controlling the oil-pressure control valve; and 
a holding-control-value-learning means, which is used for finding a holding control value by carrying out a learning process while vibrating the control signal at a predetermined amplitude when a predetermined learning condition for execution of the learning process to find the holding control value is satisfied where the holding control value is a value of the control signal for holding the valve variable quantity at a target value of the valve variable quantity.
